May 3, 2016 7:24 AM
Fort Worth should continue to catch break from major rain
Todays high 80 degrees, overnight low 56Slight chance of precipitation tonightRain chances increase late this weekend
A slight chance for rain is forecast tonight northwest of Fort Worth.
National Weather Service
Courtesy
i
By Christian Boschultcboschult@star-telegram.com
LinkedIn
Google+
Pinterest
Reddit
Print
Order Reprint of this Story
FORT WORTH
North Texas should see sunny skies, clear nights and high temperatures in the 70s and 80s through Saturday.Todays high is expected to reach 73 degrees with a low of 56 tonight, according to the National Weather Service. Meteorologist Lamont Bain said some places in Fort Worth have a small chance of precipitation, but that most areas wont see any rain. The likelihood of rain increases Saturday to 20 percent, then 30 percent Sunday and 50 percent Monday. Its still far out for specific details but it does look like well be dealing with some showers and storms, said Bain. It looks like the first part of next week itll be a favorable pattern for showers and storms.Bain said May is generally wetter than April.According to the weather service, DFW Airport received a total of 4.6 inches of rain in April. The record for the month is 17.64 inches, set in 1922.
